k about avoiding interactive terminal hangs with JLine v2 and whether I should implement fake v2 classes too for better behavior control.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Examining native test setup**\\n\\nI'm considering how the native tests will utilize ShellConsole with dynamic reflection on test classes. There's this question about whether the native image agent generates metadata, but it seems the metadata file currently lacks entries for these test classes—likely due to being generated conditionally. I think we're not supposed to update it manually. If the workflow doesn't automatically generate the metadata, the native test could fail due to missing entries for reflection. I should inspect the current metadata to clarify.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_eFRxbpUApk4SNlIrvjoA2Zi9|fc_0568128f112b68520169f51e9b9c5481a083a837b054cb76a6", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "metadata/org.mozilla/rhino/1.7R5/reachability-metadata.json", "limit": 200}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 727, "output": 1886, "cacheRead": 28160, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 30773, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777671805059, "responseId": "resp_0568128f112b68520169f51e7d826c81a0bea8eb913bd1f224"}}
