[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Creating a custom classloader**\n\nI’m considering a custom classloader solution. Instead of using the already-loaded org.mozilla.javascript.tools.shell.ShellConsole class, I could create a new classloader that only includes the rhino jar and the v1 fake JLine classes, leaving out v2. I need to load a JUnit-independent helper class too. I might want to call ShellConsole.getConsole and could explore using reflection, or maybe MethodHandles.publicLookup could be a useful approach.\n\n**Considering JLine classes**\n\nI need to create fake JLine v1 classes, but they can’t be in the same file due to package requirements. I should add additional source files. I’m wondering if these are \"test class files\"? They actually resemble production-like fixtures, so they don't have a Test suffix. I've noticed that generating one-to-one test class files might only require public JUnit top-level classes. It’s a bit confusing, but I’ll figure it out!\n\n**Considering dynamic class generation**\n\nI'm wondering if I could generate fake JLine classes at runtime using JavaCompiler. But I need to consider JVM coverage, and I want to avoid creating extra source files. Writing .java files as strings to a temporary location sounds bad. Adding a real JLine v2 dependency while keeping v1 fake packages might work, as the main test covers v2. However, I need to think about avoiding interactive terminal hangs with JLine v2 and whether I should implement fake v2 classes too for better behavior control.\n\n**Examining native test setup**\n\nI'm considering how the native tests will utilize ShellConsole with dynamic reflection on test classes. There's this question about whether the native image agent generates metadata, but it seems the metadata file currently lacks entries for these test classes—likely due to being generated conditionally. I think we're not supposed to update it manually.